From d50797049eb332a80af19651c305fdc0a824b3ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dimitri John Ledkov <dimitri.ledkov@surgut.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 10:49:40 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Remove pre-share from default TLS groups

TLS_DEFAULT_GROUP_LIST is used without openssl.cnf to provide the
default set of TLS GROUPS that are supported for handshake. This list
includes two preshares for X25519MLKEM768 and X25519 in the
ClientHello. These preshares are larger than maximum packet size,
which causes AWS firewall to drop connections.

Remove the hybrid preshare, the negotiated group will then be shared
in subsequent packets, over the connection that AWS firewall will no
longer drop.

Note that if no-preshares are elected, the first one is still
sent. Thus keep "*" on the X25519 pre-share which is the most common,
non-PQC one.

Due to historical packaging changes, default config cannot yet be
simply updated, as it was not shipped.

This patch cannot be applied before running tests, the reason for this
is as follows - if the mutually agreed preffered group is not part of
the ClientHello key-share, server will send request to change cipher
and a second larger ClientHello will be sent with the PQC
key-share. And all the tests that track and test hand-shake are not
setup to test this scenario.

We really must migrate openssl-config-fipshardened & openssl packaging
to support shipping openssl.cnf by default.

Signed-off-by: Dimitri John Ledkov <dimitri.ledkov@surgut.co.uk>
---
 ssl/t1_lib.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ssl/t1_lib.c b/ssl/t1_lib.c
index cd40fd13e8..39295d5053 100644
--- a/ssl/t1_lib.c
+++ b/ssl/t1_lib.c
@@ -206,7 +206,7 @@ static const unsigned char ecformats_all[] = {
 /* Group list string of the built-in pseudo group DEFAULT */
 #define DEFAULT_GROUP_NAME "DEFAULT"
 #define TLS_DEFAULT_GROUP_LIST \
-    "?*X25519MLKEM768 / ?*X25519:?secp256r1 / ?X448:?secp384r1:?secp521r1 / ?ffdhe2048:?ffdhe3072"
+    "?X25519MLKEM768 / ?*X25519:?secp256r1 / ?X448:?secp384r1:?secp521r1 / ?ffdhe2048:?ffdhe3072"
 
 static const uint16_t suiteb_curves[] = {
     OSSL_TLS_GROUP_ID_secp256r1,
-- 
2.51.0

